Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
report_noise(25.10)                                        report_noise(25.10)

Name
       report_noise - Generates text-based noise reports

Syntax
       report_noise

       [-help]

       [-bumpy_waveform]

       [-cell_type {bbox | clock | data | latch}]

       [-delay {min | max}]

       [-double_clocking]

       [-double_switching]

       [-exclude_failures]

       [-expand_virtual_attacker_bus]

       [-failure]

       [-gui_victim_nets_file]

       [-format <string>]

       [-histogram]

       [-level {vl | vh | vlu | vho}]

       [-max_threshold <float>]

       [-merge_dir <string>]

       [-nets <string>]

       [-output_format string]

       [-output_file <string>]

       [-overshoot_undershoot]

       [-pins <string>]

       [-precision <integer>]

       [-quiet_nets]

        [-remove_status_row <string>]

       [-report_virtual_attacker_constituents]

       [-reverse_voltage_change_threshold <float>]

       [-slack <float>]

       [-skip_nets_or_pins_in_header]

       [-sort_by <string>]

       [-style {default | extended}]

       [-threshold <float>]

       [-txtfile <filename[.gz]>]

       [-view]

       Generates text-based noise reports.

       Note:  You  need to ensure that the setSIMode -enable_glitch_report (to
       generate glitch report) or -enable_delay_report (to  generate  detailed
       delay report) parameters are set to true, before the report_timing, up-
       date_timing, or update_glitch commands are run.

Parameters
       ________________________________________________________

       | -help  |   Prints out the command usage.                 |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -bumpy |  Flags nets with bumpy waveforms at the         |

       | _wavef |   receiver.Note: This parameter will always     |

       | orm    |   show maximum delay bumpy report (even if      |

       |        |  the -delay min option is specified).           |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -cell_ |  Generates a glitch report for the              |

       | type   |   user-specified cell-type. You can specify one |

       |  {bbox |   of the following options:bbox: Generates a    |

       |  |     |   report for only the black-box receiversclock: |

       |  clock |   Generates a report for only the clock pin     |

       |  |     |   receiversdata: Generates a report for only    |

       |        |   the data pin receiverslatch: Generates a      |

       | data | |   report for only the latch pin receivers       |

       |  latch |                                                 |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -delay |  Reports delay uncertainty instead of noise     |

       |        |   values. The only legal values are min or      |

       | {min | |  max for minimum or maximum path delay          |

       |  max}  |   analysis.                                     |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -doubl |   Enables double clocking reporting.            |

       | e_cloc |                                                 |

       | king   |                                                 |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -doubl |   Repor |         |         |         |         |

       | e_swit |  ts     |         |         |         |         |

       | ching  |   doubl |         |         |         |         |

       |        |  e      |         |         |         |         |

       |        |   switc |         |         |         |         |

       |        |  hing   |         |         |         |         |

       |        |   analy |         |         |         |         |

       |        |  sis    |         |         |         |         |

       |        |         |         |         |         |         |

       |        |  data   |         |         |         |         |

       |        |   in    |         |         |         |         |

       |        |   noise |         |         |         |         |

       |        |   repor |         |         |         |         |

       |        |  ts.    |         |         |         |         |

       |________|_________|_________|_________|_________|______|

       | -exclu |  Excludes all failing nets from the glitch      |

       | de_fai |   report.                                       |

       | lures  |                                                 |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -expan |  Reports virtual attacker components and        |

       | d_virt |   expands bus bits in the noise reports.This    |

       | ual_at |   parameter works only when the bus virtual     |

       | tacker |   attacker feature is enabled using the         |

       | _bus   |   setSIMode                                     |

       |        |   -enable_virtual_attacker_constituent_report   |

       |        |   true setting.                                 |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -failu |  Reports receiver peak failures and DC          |

       | re     |   tolerance failure nets. Use this option       |

       |        |  only for glitch noise failure reports.The      |

       |        |   report_noise, without the -failure option,    |

       |        |   will use 0.10 of vdd as default.When you      |

       |        |   specify -failure option you need to use       |

       |        |   -threshold to lowest order of noise that is   |

       |        |   saved, if not specified which is 0.05 of      |

       |        |   Vdd.Option: Directory Name:-sort_by noise     |

       |        |   glitch -sort_by rcvr_peak glitch              |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -forma |  Specifies the output report format fields.     |

       | t      |   The valid fields are:arc, attacker_edge,      |

       |  strin |   attacker_logical_correlation_phase,           |

       | g      |   attacker_net, attacker_offset, attacker_peak, |

       |        |   attacker_slew, attacker_source,               |

       |        |   attacker_status, attacker_vdd,                |

       |        |   attacker_wire_length, attacker_xcap,          |

       |        |   cell_type, delay, glitch_slack, incr_delay,   |

       |        |   level, peak, receiver_cell,                   |

       |        |   receiver_input_failure_threshold,             |

       |        |   receiver_input_pin,                           |

       |        |   receiver_output_failure_threshold,            |

       |        |   receiver_output_peak, slack, slack_status,    |

       |        |   stage_info, thresh_source,                    |

       |        |   verbose_logical_correlation_report,           |

       |        |   victim_edge, victim_library,                  |

       |        |   victim_logical_correlation_phase, victim_net, |

       |        |   victim_slew, victim_total_area,               |

       |        |   victim_total_cap, victim_total_cross_cap,     |

       |        |   victim_vdd, victim_width,                     |

       |        |   victim_wire_lengthNote: The                   |

       |        |   victim_total_cross_cap option is supported    |

       |        |   only for SI delay reporting. Each field       |

       |        |   corresponds to the following columns of the   |

       |        |   glitch report:arc: Arcattacker_edge:          |

       |        |   Edgeattacker_net: Netattacker_offset:         |

       |        |  Offset (ps)attacker_peak: Peak                 |

       |        |   (mV)attacker_slew: Slew                       |

       |        |  (ps)attacker_source: Constituents:             |

       |        |   Sourceattacker_status: Statueattacker_vdd Vdd |

       |        |   (V)attacker_wire_lengthattacker_xcap: Xcap    |

       |        |   (fF)glitch_slack: Slacklevel: Levelpeak: Peak |

       |        |   (mV)receiver_cell: Receiver                   |

       |        |   cellreceiver_input_failure_threshold:         |

       |        |   Receiver Input Thresholdreceiver_input_pin:   |

       |        |   ReceiverNetreceiver_output_failure_threshold: |

       |        |   Failure thresholdreceiver_output_peak:        |

       |        |   Receiver output peak Valueslack_status:       |

       |        |   Statusstage_infothresh_source:                |

       |        |   ReceiverThresholdType (Global | User |        |

       |        |   Library)victim_library: Libraryvictim_net:    |

       |        |   VictimNetvictim_total_area:                   |

       |        |   TotalAreavictim_total_cap: TotalCap           |

       |        |   (fF)victim_vdd: Vdd (V)victim_width: Width    |

       |        |   (ps)victim_wire_lengthThe following options   |

       |        |   are not available with the single line        |

       |        |   format:delayincr_delayslackthresh_sourcevicti |

       |        |  m_edgevictim_slewvictim_total_cross_capTo      |

       |        |   choose whether the report format should be on |

       |        |   a single line or multiple lines, you can      |

       |        |  use the -output_format parameter.              |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -gui_v |   Generates the GUI format glitch reports (aae  |

       | ictim_ |  or aae_<viewname> files under the            |

       | nets_f |   reporting directory) and incremental delay    |

       | ile    |   reports (aae_<max/min>_incDelay or          |

       |        |   aae_<viewname>_<max/min>_incDelay         |

       |        |    files under the reporting directory) to be   |

       |        |   used in the Display Noise Net form.           |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -histo |   Generates the noise histogram.                |

       | gram   |                                                 |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -level |   Specifies the level for which a report needs  |

       |  {vl | |  to be generated when single-level report is    |

       |  vh    |   desired. You can specify one of these options |

       | |      |   -  vl, vh, vlu, and vho.                      |

       | vlu    |                                                 |

       | | vho} |                                                 |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -max_t |  Specifies the maximum peak noise or receiver   |

       | hresho |   peak thresholds to report on.                 |

       | ld     |                                                 |

       |  float |                                                 |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -merge |  Takes a directory name and generates a         |

       | _dir   |   software compatible database.                 |

       |  strin |                                                 |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -nets  |  Reports the specified nets in the noise        |

       | string |   report.                                       |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -outpu |  Specifies the name of the output file name     |

       | t_file |   prefix. The name of the output file is        |

       |  strin |   generated by combining the prefix and the     |

       | g      |   specified view name.If you do not specify     |

       |        |   this option:The software automatically        |

       |        |  names the text report as `glitch' for noise    |

       |        |   glitch reports and `delay' for noise delay    |

       |        |   reports.The software dumps the generated      |

       |        |   report to the console window for better       |

       |        |   usability.Note: If the text report file       |

       |        |  with the .gz extension is used, the output     |

       |        |   file is gzipped to generate a compressed      |

       |        |   report.                                       |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -pins  |   Specifies the name of the pins to be          |

       | string |   reported.                                     |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -preci |  Specifies the precision value up to which the  |

       | sion   |  glitch data is to be printed. The allowed      |

       |  integ |   values are 0, 1, 2 and 3.                     |

       | er     |                                                 |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -outpu |  Specifies if the output format should be on a  |

       | t_form |  single line or on multiple lines. You can      |

       | at     |   specify one of the following                  |

       |  strin |   options:single_linemultiple_lineIf the        |

       | g      |   single_line option is specified and the       |

       |        |   attacker info is chosen as a field, then      |

       |        |  all the attacker related format options will   |

       |        |   be printed together.The -output_format        |

       |        |   parameter only works with the -format         |

       |        |  option and does not affect the default         |

       |        |   reporting output format.Default:              |

       |        |   multiple_line                                 |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -overs |  Reports the overshoot (VHO) and undershoot     |

       | hoot_u |   (VLU) glitches.The setSIMode                  |

       | ndersh |   -enable_overshoot_undershoot_glitch must be   |

       | oot    |   set to true before the analysis is performed, |

       |        |   in order to generate the overshoot-undershoot |

       |        |   glitch report.Default: If this option is      |

       |        |  not used during glitch reporting, then VL      |

       |        |  and VH type of glitches will be reported.      |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -quiet |   Generates a report of all the quiet           |

       | _nets  |   attackers.                                    |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -remov |   Shows only the active attackers and filters   |

       | e_stat |   out Sb, UF, and LC from the glitch report.    |

       | us_row |                                                 |

       |  <st   |                                                 |

       | ring;G |                                                 |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -repor |  Specifies the maximum slack value for a bumpy  |

       | t_virt |  net.                                           |

       | ual_at |                                                 |

       | tacker |                                                 |

       | _const |                                                 |

       | ituent |                                                 |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -rev   |  Reports the clock nets with reverse swing      |

       | everse |   greater than the user-specified threshold     |

       | _volta |   value (ratio of VDD). By default, the         |

       | ge_cha |   threshold value is set to 0.1.                |

       | nge_th |                                                 |

       | reshol |                                                 |

       | d      |                                                 |

       |  <fl   |                                                 |

       | oat> |                                                 |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -slack |  Generates a report for bumpy nets based on     |

       |  float |   slack.Units: Seconds                          |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -skip_ |   Generates the glitch report without a list    |

       | nets_o |   of nets or pins in the report header.         |

       | r_pins |                                                 |

       | _in_he |                                                 |

       | ader   |                                                 |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -sort_ |  Requests the sorting of entries. You can sort  |

       | by     |  by:noisereceiver_peakslackcell_typeThe         |

       |  strin |   software determines the default HTML output   |

       | g      |   directories based on the options you          |

       |        |   choose.Depending on the sorting option you    |

       |        |   select, the software sorts the report         |

       |        |  fields in the following order:-sort_by         |

       |        |  Option Level 1 Level 2 Level 3 Level           |

       |        |   4rcvr_peak receiver peak noise netname        |

       |        |   level noise noise - netname level             |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       |        |  For example, if you use the -sort_bynoise      |

       |        |   option, the first level of sorting will be    |

       |        |   based on noise, followed by receiver peak,    |

       |        |   netname, and level.Note: The report           |

       |        |  displays the vl noise level before the vh      |

       |        |   noise level.Default: receiver_peak            |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -style |  Generates reports in one of the styles -       |

       |  {defa |   extended or default.extended: Generates       |

       | ult    |   extended reports with victim and aggressor    |

       | |      |   timing windows, dropped aggressor slews,      |

       |  exten |  and reasons for dropped aggressors.            |

       | ded}   |   Additionally, the report also shows driver    |

       |        |   pins and driver library pins.default:         |

       |        |   Generates the default report, which is        |

       |        |   similar to the text report generated using    |

       |        |   the -text parameter.                          |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -thres |  Specifies the minimum peak noise, absolute     |

       | hold   |   delay uncertainty, relative delay             |

       |  float |   uncertainty, and receiver peak thresholds     |

       |        |  to report on.Default:0.10 of vdd for nets -    |

       |        |   when the glitch report is generated using the |

       |        |   report_noise-sort_by noise option.10 (ps) for |

       |        |   nets - when a detailed delay report is        |

       |        |   generated using the report_noise-delay        |

       |        |   parameter).Note:The -threshold parameter      |

       |        |   accepts percentage values.All -sort_by values |

       |        |   that represent voltages will be in mV.        |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -txtfi |  Specifies the name of the text report file.    |

       | le     |    If the specified file name is compressed,    |

       |  filen |   with the .gz extension, the file is           |

       | ame[.g |   gzipped.If you do not specify the -txtfile    |

       | z]     |   option:The software automatically names the   |

       |        |   text report as `glitch' for noise glitch      |

       |        |   reports and `delay' for noise delay           |

       |        |   reports.The software dumps the generated      |

       |        |   report to the console window for better       |

       |        |   usability.If the -txtfile parameter is not    |

       |        |   used, then Innovus will output the SI         |

       |        |  report to the screen. When the -txtfile        |

       |        |   parameter is specified, then Innovus uses the |

       |        |   user-specified name. In case of MMMC, Innovus |

       |        |   uses the <txtfile Name>_<view Name>       |

       |        |   naming convention.                            |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       | -view  |   Specifies the view name.                      |

       |________________________________________________|______|

       Examples
              * The  following  command  reports  noise for the view named de-
                fault_emulate_view:

                report_noise  -delay  max   -threshold   1600   -txtfile   de-
                lay_max_format.rpt  -format {attacker_slew  attacker_xcap  at-
                tacker_status attacker_edge    attacker_net  stage_info  slack
                victim_slew  victim_total_cross_cap victim_net }

